This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 11th as Patriot Day and National Day of Service and Remembrance. The proclamation commemorates the terrorist attacks on September 11, 2001, and encourages Americans to honor the victims and heroes of that day by serving their communities. It calls for displaying the American flag at half-staff, participating in community service, and observing a moment of silence at 8:46 a.m., the time the first plane struck the World Trade Center. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of unity and compassion in the face of adversity.